{
  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "Training Details Continued PretrainingEarly studies on pretrained language models show that continued pretraining in a specific domain is beneficial for downstream task performance [24,25,[64][65][66].",
    "Several studies found that continued pretraining of a language model on the unlabeled data of a given task improves the model's end-task performance [67][68][69].",
    "In the medical domain, the most similar work to ours is PMC-Llama [27], which adapts the Llama model through continued pretraining onPubMed Central papers and medical textbooks.",
    "In contrast to prior works, MEDITRON studies the benefit of continued pretraining at the 70B scale and shows that expanding the domainspecific pretraining data and aligning it with clinical practice guidelines significantly improves downstream tasks and physician evaluations.We adopt most modeling and pretraining settings from the Llama-2 study [4].",
    "For the model architecture, we inherit the standard transformer architecture, the use of RMSNorm, the SwiGLU activation function, and rotary position embeddings directly from the implementation of Llama."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
